Description: Schecter TSH-1 Semi hollow body. Diamond Series Mfg 2001- 2004 (Korea) Original Version TSH -1 from Schecter when it came from the factory with a mahogany body, bolt-on maple neck, Seymour Duncan designed bridge humbucker and Seymour Duncan designed P-90 in the neck position. Super nice condition. You would have to study it carefully to determine it is not new. Pictures are just assorted views of the instrument and do not intend to point out any blems or issues. Any defects appearing in pictures is due to lighting. No case but will be packed well. Plays and sounds great. From the web: This is a very versatile guitar that sounds great for Blues, Rock, Country. Having a P90 (neck position) as well as a Humbucker (bridge position) gives you so many tonal variations. Combined with having the Semi-Hollowbody, all tones are possible. A really great playing guitar. Grover Tuners, Diamond inlay fret markers. A flame maple top on mahogany gives this semi-hollow body guitar a deluxe look even from a distance, and a host of other appointments finish the job: cream binding on body and neck, diamond position markers, a tune-o-matic/Trapeze bridge and tailpiece, medium-jumbo frets, and a selection of transparent finishes.
